---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility"
  description="RevAudio's accessibility commitment, conformance status, known limitations, and how to report a barrier."
>
  <section class="plugin-detail">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;">
      <h1>Accessibility</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last reviewed: 2026-06-28</p>

      <h2>Our commitment</h2>
      <p>
        We want everyone to be able to browse, evaluate, and buy RevAudio plugins &mdash; including people who
        use a keyboard only, a screen reader, magnification, or other assistive technology. We aim to meet the
        <strong>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA</strong>, and we treat accessibility
        as an ongoing part of building this site, not a one-off task.
      </p>

      <h2>What we&rsquo;ve done</h2>
      <p>This site is built to be usable without a mouse and without our visual styling. In particular:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A &ldquo;skip to main content&rdquo; link and clear, visible keyboard focus on every control.</li>
        <li>Semantic headings, landmarks, and labels so screen readers can navigate structure and forms.</li>
        <li>A built-in <strong>high-contrast mode</strong> &mdash; the toggle sits at the bottom-left of every page.</li>
        <li>Respect for your system <em>reduced-motion</em> setting: animations are dropped when you ask for less motion.</li>
        <li>Support for operating-system high-contrast / forced-colors modes.</li>
        <li>Text alternatives for meaningful images, and colour that is never the only way information is conveyed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Conformance status</h2>
      <p>
        This site is <strong>partially conformant</strong> with WCAG 2.1 AA: it meets most success criteria, and
        we are actively closing the remaining gaps. &ldquo;Partially conformant&rdquo; means some content may not
        yet fully meet the standard, which we are honest about below.
      </p>

      <h2>Known limitations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Checkout &amp; payment.</strong> Purchases are handled by a third-party payment provider. Their
          checkout is outside our direct control and may not fully match our accessibility target. If you hit a
          barrier at payment, contact us &mdash; we will help you complete your purchase another way.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Product wordmarks.</strong> Stylised plugin names (for example the &ldquo;Rev&rdquo; in
          RevLimiter) are brand lettering. We have raised their contrast, and the surrounding content is fully
          readable.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Audio demos.</strong> Where we publish audio, it is illustrative; the same information is given
          in text on the product page.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How this was assessed</h2>
      <p>
        Most recently reviewed on <strong>28 June 2026</strong> using a combination of automated testing
        (axe-core, against WCAG 2.1 A and AA) and manual checks &mdash; keyboard-only navigation, focus order and
        visibility, reduced-motion behaviour, and form labelling. We re-check when we ship significant changes.
      </p>

      <h2>Tell us about a barrier</h2>
      <p>
        If something on this site blocks you, or you need information or a feature in a different accessible
        format, please email <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> with the page address
        and a short description of the problem. We aim to reply <strong>within two business days</strong> and to
        work with you to give you the content or complete your task in an accessible way. Your feedback also goes
        straight onto our fix list.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
